  "texts": [
    "Finally, we pair these human-written documents with essays generated using GPT-3.5 and GPT-4.",
    "We set the temperature (randomness-in-response hyperparameter 2) to 1.20 (min = 0; max = 2.0).",
    "We generated 25 essays for each temperature setting of increments of 0.1 and found that 1.2 produced the best results across the essay prompts and formats.",
    "Focusing on GPT 3.5 and GPT-4 also gave us additional control by standardizing the temperature hyperparameter instead of estimating temperature settings across models.",
    "We found that texts generated with temperatures above 1.20 were more likely to include irrelevant or random text, and unicode errors (e.g., \"haci\\u8db3 foot_2 \" was included in an essay generated with a temperature of 1.6)."
  ],
